OAuth / Subscription Credential Files
======================================

These files are bind-mounted directly into worker containers so that
token rotations (e.g. refresh tokens) propagate to all workers instantly.
Logging in manually inside one worker authenticates all future (and
existing running) workers.

API keys (always-valid, no rotation) remain in .env.

Setup:
  cp -r .cred.example .cred

Then fill in the files below as needed. Leave as {} if unused.

claude.json
-----------
Path in worker: ~/.claude/.credentials.json
Contents: OAuth credentials JSON from your Claude Pro/Max subscription.
  macOS:  security find-generic-password -s "Claude Code-credentials" -w
  Linux:  cat ~/.claude/.credentials.json
Or start a worker, run `claude` to log in interactively — the credentials
will be written back to this file automatically.

codex.json
----------
Path in worker: ~/.codex/auth.json
Contents: Codex auth.json from your ChatGPT Plus/Pro subscription.
  Run `codex login` locally, then copy ~/.codex/auth.json contents here.
Or start a worker, run `codex --login` to log in interactively.

gemini.json
-----------
Path in worker: ~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json
Contents: Gemini OAuth credentials from your Google account.
  Run `gemini` locally, select "Login with Google", then copy the
  contents of ~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json here.
Or start a worker, run `gemini` to log in interactively.
